ecular and faith-oriented-understand what drives individuals and communities to welcome refugees with open hearts and open arms, the authors hope to inspire people across Canada and beyond its borders to strengthen our collective willingness and ability to offer refuge as a lifesaving protection for those who need it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChurch work with refugeeszOntariozOttawa. 0aRefugeesxServices forzOntariozOttawa. 0aSyrianszOntariozOttawa. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Immigration.2bisacsh  aSettlement.  aactivism.  arefugee settlement sector.  arefugee settlement.  arefugee sponsorship.  arefugees.  asponsorship.  avolunteerism.1 aJuma, Karina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTellier, Geneviève, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTerretta, Meredith, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780776629711?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780776629711zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780776629711/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA